{
  "texts": [
    "However, they may not perform as well as attention-based models in tasks requiring selective attention.",
    "Memory neural networks (Tang et al. 2016b; Chen et al. 2017) are designed to store and retrieve information over long sequences, making them suitable for tasks with extensive context.",
    "However, they can be complex to train and require significant computational resources.",
    "Pre-trained language models have emerged as the predominant foundation for the ABSC task.",
    "Sun et al. (2019) innovatively refrains the ABSC task as a sentence pair classification problem by introducing an auxiliary sentence."
  ]
}